This paper discusses OLTP systems and their high-throughput requirements, which are typically studied in the database (cs.DB) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-categories. The use of GPGPU for transaction executions is a topic that falls under the computer architecture (cs.AR) sub-category. The paper also discusses optimization techniques, which are commonly studied in the numerical analysis (cs.NA) and computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE) sub-categories.
